text: Well if pucatrade wasn't dead before it is now. They're charging dues to free accounts each month now. It's like they don't want to build theyre user base at all
Yeah. I stopped using them a year ago. I shouldn't have to pay a bounty because a card is desirable. The service quickly turned into a joke.

I used them for about 2 years. I traded quite a bit of cards though there, probably around 800-900 dollars worth. It was fantastic at first. Even got a few high dollar cards like mana crypt and imperial recruiter. But the bounty stuff destroyed the marketplace. It's pretty much just lgs getting rid of junk cards and buying chase rares
Yeah. I got my tarmagoyf and snapcaster playsets on there like the first year it was up. Also 3 liliana of the veil. Year 2 was a rapid decline and by year 3 I was done.

True story, I had a kid send me a tarmagoyf in a penny sleeve inside a normal envelope with no protection or bracing. It got bent so I had to open a case that took PT over 8 weeks to resolve. Their resolution? Refund me the points after I pay to send them the jacked up tarm. 8 weeks for that.

Yea I had someone say they were sending me a Xiou Dun. It never came after a month so I opened a ticket. 4 Months later they deemed that was enough time for the card to come and finally gave me my points back
